    <activity>
        <introduction><p>We will consider the function <m>\displaystyle \frac{4x+8}{x}</m>.</p></introduction>
        <task>
            <p>Compute the limit <m>\displaystyle  \lim_{x\to \infty} \frac{4x+8}{x}</m>.</p>
        <ol label="A">
            <li><m>0</m></li>
            <li><m>8</m></li>
            <li><m>1</m></li>
            <li><m>4</m></li>
        </ol>            
        </task>
        <task>
            <p>What value does <m>f(x)</m> converge to as <m>x\to\infty</m>?</p>
        <ol label="A">
            <li><m>0</m></li>
            <li><m>8</m></li>
            <li><m>1</m></li>
            <li><m>4</m></li>
        </ol>               
        </task>
        <task>
            <p>Determine on which intervals <m>f(x)</m> is increasing and/or decreasing.</p>
        </task>
        <task>
            <p>Which statement best describes <m>f(x)</m> for <m>x>0</m>?</p>
          <ol label="A">
            <li><m>f(x)</m> is bounded above by 4</li>
            <li><m>f(x)</m> is bounded below by 4</li>
            <li><m>f(x)</m> is bounded above and below by 4</li>
            <li><m>f(x)</m> is not bounded above</li>
            <li><m>f(x)</m> is not bounded below</li>
          </ol>   
        </task>
        <task>
            <p>Determine on which intervals <m>f(x)</m> is concave up and/or concave down.</p>
        </task>
        <task><p>Sketch a graph of the function <m>f(x)</m>.</p></task>
    </activity>

